<HEADLINE> African Parliaments' Union to Meet in Harare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Parliament of Zimbabwe will
host a two-day special conference of the Union of African
Parliaments (UAP) to promote their cooperation, the Zimbabwe News
Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The UAP is a parliamentary organization and its goal is to
strengthen the role and prestige of parliamentary institutions in
Africa and to further the objectives of the Organization of
African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
A statement from the parliament of Zimbabwe said Sunday that
the conference would be held on Wednesday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 participants from both English and French
speaking countries in Africa are expected to attend the
gathering.
</P>
<P>
Major topics to be discussed include the strengthening of the
UAP as a mechanism for inter-parliamentary cooperation in Africa
and its role in consolidating democracy on the continent.
</P>
<P>
Key speakers for the conference have been drawn from the OAU,
the United Nations and its Economic Commission for Africa.
</P>
<P>
The member countries will also elect a president and
vice-president for the UAP at the coming conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
