<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peruvian Plane Crash Kills At Least 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- A Peruvian air force cargo plane
carrying dozens of civilian passengers crashed Sunday in northern
Peru, killing at least 12 people, officials said.
</P>
<P>
"The plane was carrying about 40 passengers. It seems between
15 and 20 people have died," Miguel Ciccia, a congressman told
Radio Programas, a local radio station.
</P>
<P>
But police could not confirm the death toll. A local hospital
director said that 12 people were killed and 39 others injured
when the Russian-made Antonov plane went down.
</P>
<P>
The plane was carrying refugees stranded by El Nino-driven
flooding from the city of Tumbes to Piura in northern Peru, an AP
report said.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft split in two pieces as it went down into a canal
about two kilometers from the Piura airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
