<HEADLINE> UN Secretary-General Visits Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 29 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan arrived here Sunday on a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
According to Itar-Tass news agency, during his visit Annan will
meet with Russian President Boris Yeltsin, Foreign Minister
Yevgeny Primakov and deputies of the State Duma.
</P>
<P>
Among other international problems, Annan will inform the work
of the international commission on Iraqi disarmament and the
inspection of presidential sites in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
According to Spokesman of the Russian Foreign Ministry Gennady
Tarasov, The forthcoming talks between the Russian leadership and
Kofi Anna aim to consolidate the U.N. central role in the
settlement of crises, including the support to efforts for
settling conflicts in the Commonwealth of Independent States
(CIS).
</P>
<P>
U.N. chief and Russian leaders also plan to discuss ways to
upgrade the interaction between Russian and the United Nations
Organization in order to raise the efficiency of the U.N. and
increase its potential in the provision of peace, stability and
international cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
