<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Trade Body Sets up Mideast Regional Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, March 29 (Xinhua) -- The Paris-based International Trade
Chamber (ITC) has set up its Middle East regional council to boost
commercial, banking, insurance and other business cooperation
among its member countries, an ITC official said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, Syria, Lebanon and the Saudi Arabia have become the
first batch of countries winning the regional council membership
which is limited to the Arab countries in the region only,
Mohammad Asfur, President of ITC Amman Chapter, was quoted by
Jordan's official news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The council would hold general assembly annually and its
headquarters would be based in Lebanon in the first phase of
operation and then move to Jordan in the next phase, according to
Asfur.
</P>
<P>
The first general assembly of the regional council, to be
convened in Beirut in October this year, will settle down
relevant regulations for its operation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ITC was encouraging other Arab countries in the
region to set up national chapters and then join the regional
council so as to benefit from its global network established long
ago for business cooperation, said Asfur.
</P>
<P>
The ITC, a Paris-based world trade organization, has regional
councils all over the world. All the councils can benefit from
publications and research studies issued by the Paris headquarters
on topics such as global agriculture, sea transport, insurance,
arbitration and international trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
