<HEADLINE> Mzee Re-appointed Zanzibar Electoral Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 29 (Xinhua) -- President of Zanzibar Dr.
Salmin Amour has re-appointed Zubeir Juma Mzee as Chairman of the
Zanzibar Electoral Commission (ZEC), the Monday edition of the
Daily News paper available to Xinhua reported.
</P>
<P>
However, it did not say when Mzee was re-appointed.
</P>
<P>
The electoral commission is charged with a responsibility for
the election of the president, members of the House of
Representatives and local councillors in the Zanzibar isles.
</P>
<P>
Mzee was first appointed ZEC chairman in March of 1995 after
the opposition party Civic United Front (CUF) declared that it
had no confidence in the commission.
</P>
<P>
President Amour, a member of the Tanzanian ruling party CCM,
has also appointed six new members of the commission. Meanwhile,
he has appointed Khamis Ali Ameir as the new director of
elections.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar, a part of the United Republic of Tanzania, is
located in the Indian Ocean off the east coast of the mainland of
the African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
