<HEADLINE> 1stadd: Huge Explosion in Ramallah Kills Two </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 29 (Xinhua) -- A huge explosion blasted Sunday
night in the West Bank city Ramallah, killing two people and
injured several others, Israeli army radio said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place in a residential neighborhood where
the office of Jibril Rajoub, a Palestinian official in charge of
security in the West Bank, is situated. The cause of the explosion
was not immediate known, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian police have recently smashed seven bomb factories
run by the militant organization Islamic Resistance Movement
(Hamas) in Gaza Strip. It is not known whether the blast has any
connection with that crackdown.
</P>
<P>
The city of Ramallah, in the north of Jerusalem, plays host to
several ministries of the Palestinian National Authority. 
