<HEADLINE> Eastern China Province Improving Customs Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province will
simplify procedures even more to become more efficient in clearing
goods, because of its expanding foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Yang Shuilai, director of the provincial ports administration,
speaking today at a provincial port conference, said that the
coastal province's 47 airports and coastal ports handled 19.8
million tons of cargo last year, a 35.6 percent increase from the
previous year. They also handled 804,000 containers last year, an
annual rise of 34.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
He urged the ports of Zhangzhou, Putian, and Ningde to combine
a number of offices so that customers do not have to go to a
number of different places just to get one thing done as they do
now.
</P>
<P>
The most efficient port in the province so far is Xiamen, but
it should improve its computer system so that all its work can be
done without paper, Yang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
