<HEADLINE> China Continues to Open up Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Dai Xianglong, governor of the
People's Bank of China, the country's central bank, said that the
opening-up of the financial sector will continue even with the
financial crisis in some Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
Dai made the remark today at a ceremony for a new coin that
will commemorate Dr. Norman Bethune, the Canadian doctor who helped
China during World War II.
</P>
<P>
The opening drive will continue at varying speeds, Dai said,
and the gradual movement will guarantee overseas investors'
interests.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China plans to increase its Renminbi (RMB)
loans for enterprises with overseas investment.  
