<HEADLINE> Everything Ready for EC Subsector Elections in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Everything is ready for the
Election Committee (EC) subsector elections to be held here on
April 2 after about 140,000 poll cards have been sent to voters.
</P>
<P>
Leaflets carrying personal particulars of candidates have also
been mailed to voters of 35 subsectors representing various
trades, professions, labor and social service sectors, the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference and district-based
organizations, according to the Registration and Electoral
Office.
</P>
<P>
Noting that voting is simple, a spokesman for the Registration
and Electoral Office said: "all a voter needs to do is to bring
along his identity card and visit his designated polling station."
</P>
<P>
Ninety polling stations throughout Hong Kong will be open from
7.30 a.m. to 10.30 p.m. on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Large posters bearing photographs of candidates and an album
containing personal particulars of candidates will be made
available at polling stations for voters' easy reference, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Given that the polling day will fall on a working day, the
spokesman urged employers to give permission to their employees to
cast their votes during office hours.
</P>
<P>
As 95 members on the Election Committee have already been
returned from four uncontested subsectors, 963 candidates from 31
subsectors will run for 588 seats.
</P>
<P>
These 683 members will join 77 ex-officio members and 40
members nominated by the Religious Subsector to form an 800-member
Election Committee which will be responsible for electing 10
Legislative Council members on May 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
