<HEADLINE> Romania to Use Foreign Loans in Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government will
use foreign loans and allow foreign investment in housing projects.
</P>
<P>
Nicolae Noica, minister of public works and territorial
planning, said that the government plans to provide housing for as
many people as possible, the "Romania Libera" daily reports on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Up to 70 percent of the population will be able to own a house,
the minister said.
</P>
<P>
A government draft plan on national housing fund says that the
housing fund will be re-organized and a new institutional
framework will be created following free market principles.
</P>
<P>
He said the money his ministry receives from the government
budget is only enough to construct 4,000 apartments.
</P>
<P>
In order to build more houses, international tenders will be
held and a government-guaranteed foreign loan amounting to 340
million U.S. dollars will be used.
</P>
<P>
Two foreign loans totaling 360 million U.S. dollars will be used
for welfare housing.
</P>
<P>
Romania has about 270 million square meters of housing,
averaging 12 square meters per head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
