<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 14:47 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 4 Injured in Floods in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Floods triggered by torrential
rain over the past few days killed one people and injured four
others in Iran's western province of Lorestan, the official
Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Residential units of over 70 villages in the province suffered
damages of varied degrees caused by floods, which cut off roads to
560 villages and destroyed orchards and farmlands, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
In the province of Chaharmahal and Bakhtiari, floods inundated
12 villages, damaging or totally destroying 30 residential units,
ruining farmlands and gardens and knocking off power and water
supply in the surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in the central province of Isfahan, more than 200
residential units and local bridges were totally destroyed and
more than 500 heads of livestock perished as a result of the
floods, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Floods also submerged over 200 hectares of farmlands in the
southwestern province of Khuzestan and cut off gas supply to some
cities and towns, the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
