<HEADLINE> Woman Boxer Wins Discrimination Suit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Women's world welterweight
champion Jane Couch won a legal battle as an industrial tribunal
ruled on Monday that the British Boxing Board of Control was wrong
to refuse to grant a woman boxer a licence.
</P>
<P>
The tribunal rejected the boards' argument that pre-menstrual
tension made women unstable and ruled in favor of Couch.
</P>
<P>
Couch was supported by Britain's Equal Opportunities Commission
which said she was being denied the opportunity to box
professionally because of her sex.
</P>
<P>
The commission said victory in the courts would open the door
of professional boxing to all suitably qualified women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
