<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao on United Front, Multi-Party Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau,
speaking today at the opening ceremony of a course on theory and
practice of the United Front and multi-party cooperation, urged
greater understanding of the political significance of perfecting
multi-party cooperation and political consultation.
</P>
<P>
He said that study should be linked reality by Deng Xiaoping
Theory's ideas on the United Front in the New Period to enhance
the ideological base of multi-party cooperation and political
consultation and advance the great cause of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The CPC-led multi-party cooperation and political consultation
system are a principal political system of China and one with
great vitality, Hu said. The farther the country's great cause goes
forward, the greater the effort of perfecting the system.
</P>
<P>
The CPC and non-communist party officials should understand the
significance of consolidating and developing the Patriotic United
Front and of perfecting multi-party cooperation and political
consultation, he said, and urged all CPC and non-communist party
members to study Deng Xiaoping Theory, which he called a guide for
all CPC work and action.
</P>
<P>
The course is being attended by 83 leading officials of the
non-Communist parties and provincial, autonomous region, and
municipality United Front departments. 
