<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clashes Erupt in West Bank on Land Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Palestinians marking the 22nd
anniversary of the Land Day clashed with Israeli troops in the
West Bank cities of Bethlehem and Ramallah on Monday. At least 10
people were injured.
</P>
<P>
The Jerusalem Media and Communication Center, an East
Jerusalem-based Palestinian press service, reported that a large
number of Palestinians clashed with Israeli troops near the
Rachel's Tomb in Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli troops fired tear gas and rubber bullets to
disperse the Palestinians, wounding seven people, JMCC said.
</P>
<P>
Three Palestinian youths were reportedly injured by rubber
bullets in clashes with Israeli troops at the Maloufuyeh
check-point near Ramallah Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
On March 30, 1976, six Israeli Arabs lost their lives in
clashes with Israel soldiers over a land dispute erupted following
Israeli government's decision to confiscate land owned by Arab
villagers in the Galilee area in northern Israel.
</P>
<P>
Both Israeli Arabs and Palestinians mark the incident each year
to protest against the land policy of the Israeli government.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Council has called on all
Palestinians inside Palestine and elsewhere to commemorate the
anniversary on Monday with popular and mass demonstrations.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police and defense forces are on high alert Monday on
both sides of the 1967 ceasefire line, also known as the Green
Line, as Israeli Arabs plan a series of strikes, marches and
demonstrations to mark the Land Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
