</P>
<P>
-- Cambodia's ousted co-premier Prince Norodom Ranariddh
returned to Phnom Penh Sunday, almost nine months after he was
toppled from power while out of the country and went into exile.
Analysts said his return was another step toward the goal of a
free and fair poll on July 26, but they added that more problems
and political tensions were inevitable.
</P>
