<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting Erupts in S. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting is being
reported in and around Somalia's southern port town of Kismaio
between forces from the Marehan subclan and those of Majerten
subclan dominating the town.
</P>
<P>
Early reports said nearly 200 heavily armed men from the
Marehan subclan stormed into the town just before dawn Monday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Loud noise from rocket propelled grenades, attack F-1 hand
grenades, heavy machine guns and assault rifles has terrorized
and awakened in bewilderment the town residents.
</P>
<P>
According to a radio operator in the town of Kismaio, 500 km
south of the capital, the fighting continued until 11:00 am
(local time) Monday morning as the Majerten, Ogaden and
Dhulbahante militiamen on one side fought bitterly against the
invaders.
</P>
<P>
The fighting spread to the village of Gobwein, about 9 km
north of the town, at 9:00 am as the invading militiamen of
Marehan started to retreat backwards.
</P>
<P>
There is no exact number of casualties so far, but the radio
operators are speaking about the death of more than 30 people,
mainly civilians, while nearly 75 others are hospitalized in
Kismaio for gunshot wounds.
</P>
<P>
"Two of my brothers and my cousin have all died in the
fighting last night," said one of the radio operators in the
town.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the town said the dead and the wounded collected
from the streets of Kismaio are from both sides, but it is
believed that the retreating militiamen have also taken some of
their wounded men with them.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that the clashes seemed to have subsided
with each side worrying about their losses.
</P>
<P>
This unprecedented fighting could be characterized as one of
the worst and most catastrophic armed clashes between the two
groups ever since the Marehan militiamen were driven out of the
town last year.
</P>
<P>
The town of Kismaio has been a focal poin for armed
insurgencies between the two sides ever since misunderstanding
arose over the control of the key positions of the town, the air
and seaports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
