<HEADLINE> Hijacker of Turkish Cypriot Airlines Plane Seized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A hijacker of a Boeing 727
passenger plane of the Turkish Cypriot Airlines was arrested in
Ankara, capital of Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that after the plane for the flight from
Girne, northern Cyprus, to Ankara took off from the divided
island on 12:05 local time (09:05 GMT), the 20-year-old Hijacker,
Mehmet Erturk, moved to the cockpit of the plane and told
Captain Pilot Soner Cabuker: "There is a bomb in my body and the
plane must fly to Bonn."
</P>
<P>
However, when Cabuker flew the plane into the Turkish
airspace, he told the Ankara Esenboga Airport that the plane
would land on the Esenboga Airport.
</P>
<P>
Turkish policemen immediately entered into the plane after
it landed safely on the airport and arrested the hijacker.
</P>
<P>
Erturk, born in Sanliurfa, southeastern Turkey, said that he
was jobless and wanted to go to Germany to find a job.
</P>
</TEXT>
