<HEADLINE> Sprint Queen Jones Set to Take Challenge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, Southwestern China, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Women's world
100m sprint champion Marion Jones is set to compete in a "world
fastest woman" race here in May.
</P>
<P>
The American sprinter's agent has comfirmed that Jones will
dash for honor in a 30,000 capacity stadium in the capital of
Sichuan province, the Chinese Athletics Association said here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jones, who won the 100m dash in 10.76 seconds at the 1997 world
championships in Athens, will face challenge from the Chinese top
sprinter Li Xuemei, who ran the year's world second best time of
10.79 in the Chinese National Games in October last year.
</P>
<P>
The other runners expected to show up in the Chengdu race are
double Olympic champion Gail Devers of the United States, Zhanna
Pintussevich of Ukraine, runner-up to Jones in the Athens Worlds,
bronze medalist Sevatheda Fynes of the Bahamas, and 200m silver
medalist Susanthika Jayasinghe of Sri Lanka. 
