Chissano, said that China is ready to make a concerted effort with
Mozambique to develop a long-term, stable and all-round
cooperative relationship oriented towards the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chissano arrived here Saturday for a week's visit as Jiang's
guest. Jiang said that he believes the visit will increase mutual
understanding and have a strong impact on relations between the
two nations.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two people have a deep traditional friendship
and bilateral ties that have withstood the test of the time and
the changing international situation.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries opened diplomatic ties, he said, they
have maintained friendly cooperative relations and always
cooperated and supported each other on international affairs.
</P>
<P>
