<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyclonic Storm Lashes India's Tornado-hit areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A cyclonic storm accompanied by
torrential rain lashed the Tornado-hit areas in the eastern Indian
State of West Bengal on Monday, reported the Press Trust of India
(PTI).
</P>
<P>
The storm, with a wind speed of 70 kmph and heavy showers,
paralysed relief operations and normal life in the district of
Midnapore, which was ripped last week by Tornado that killed 175
people and injured thousands.
</P>
<P>
However, there is no report of new casualties in the
storm-ripped area.
</P>
<P>
The storm, triggered by a low pressure along West Bengal coast,
uprooted trees, blew away thatched houses, and snapped electric
wires and telecommunication links, according to the PTI report
from the area.
</P>
<P>
Tarpaulin sheets and straw which were used in temporary sheds
to house the homeless were blown off, said Midnapore District
Magistrate Arun Bal, adding that villagers have been moved to
safer places.
</P>
<P>
Civil defense personnel, fire brigade and police have been
deployed to clear the debris in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
