<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The police have arrested
more than 50 people after hundreds of rioters burned two
government vehicles and attacked offices of the Tanzanian ruling
party Chama Cha Mapinduzi (CCM) in Dar es Salaam Sunday
afternoon, local newspapers said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The riot, the second in seven weeks, happened in areas near
the Mwembechai Mosque in the downtown, where mobsters, mostly
young men set fire on two government-owned vehicles.
</P>
<P>
They have also ransacked CCM offices at Mwembechai, Ndugumbi,
Makurumla and Kagera Mikoroshoni areas. The Ndugumbi office was
burnt.
</P>
<P>
Police and the Field Force Unit used tear gas to disperse the
mob who are armed with clubs, stones.
</P>
<P>
The Morogoro Road, where the mosque is located, was closed
until 7:45 pm after the security order came back to normal.
</P>
<P>
The riot is reported to have happened after the police banned
a meeting of the Committee for Moslem Women on Saturday.
Recently, some 16 Moslem women, acquitted of charges in the
Mwembechai riot case last month, demanded an apology from the
government for being maltreated in custody by the police.
</P>
<P>
The women were held during a violent riot near the Mwembechai
Mosque in mid-February in Dar es Salaam, in which two people,
including a Moslem school teacher, were killed, and more than 200
people were arrested.  
</P>
</TEXT>
