<HEADLINE> Five Tanzanian Women Missing after Canoe Capsizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 30 (Xinhua) -- A boat capsized in the
Indian Ocean near Tanzania's Island of Pemba, leaving five women
missing, Daily News reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The South Pemba Regional Police Commander, Hamdan Ali Uledi,
told the paper that the ill-fated boat was sailing Saturday from
Makungwe to Makombeni village when sea tide became turbulent with
a storm.
</P>
<P>
The sea disaster, the first this year, struck the 20-people
boat at 10 am after it sailed only a kilometer away from the
shore. Fifteen people managed to swim to the bank while the five
women were missing, Uledi said.
</P>
<P>
The missing persons, who are feared dead, have been identified
as Mchanga Ramadhan Komobo, 15, Fatuma Mwalimu Haji, 15, Nueza
Vuai, 20, and Kazija Makame, 15. The fifth has so far not been
identified.
</P>
<P>
This is the second boat incident reported in one week in
Tanzania. Last Wednesday a canoe sailing in Lake Victoria
capsized, leaving one person dead and seven others missing.
</P>
</TEXT>
