<HEADLINE> Premier Zhu Rongji Meets Mozambican President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji said
today that China is willing to share its experience in economic
construction with Mozambique and work together with the country to
elevate bilateral ties in all fields to a new height.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the remarks in a meeting this afternoon with
visiting Mozambican President Joaquim Alberto Chissano, who is on
a week-long visit to China as the guest of Chinese president Jiang
Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Calling President Chissano "an old friend of the Chinese
people", Zhu said that the Chinese side attaches great importance
to Chissano's current China trip and believes that his visit would
boost the friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Mozambique have enjoyed a stable
political relationship since the two countries forged diplomatic
ties 23 years ago. China values its relations with Mozambique and
regards the country as a "reliable friend".
</P>
<P>
Chissano said Zhu had made a good explanation of the policy of
the new Chinese government at a press conference soon after he
became the Chinese premier. "I have noticed the determination of
the Chinese government to step up reforms and open wider to the
outside world, as well as the bright prospects of Mozambique-China
relations", Chissano told Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on further enhancing
bilateral economic and trade links. Apart from cooperation between
the two governments, Zhu said, the Chinese government also
encourages Chinese enterprises to seek cooperative projects that
have resources and markets in Mozambique, medium-sized and small
assembly plants in particular.
</P>
<P>
Chissano voiced his admiration to China for its economic
achievements and said that his nation is ready to draw on China's
experience in governing and building the country. He hoped for
increased cooperation between the state-owned and the private-run
enterprises of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chissano and Zhu also briefed each other on their respective
domestic economic situations.
</P>
<P>
China is pleased with and appreciates Mozambique's economic
progress and its positive role in regional affairs, the Chinese
premier said. 
</P>
