<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New-Term Membership of HKCPEC Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region Monday announced the appointment of
the new-term membership of the Hong Kong Committee for Pacific
Economic Cooperation (HKCPEC) for two years, effective from April
1 this year.
</P>
<P>
William Fung, Group Managing Director of Li and Fund Limited,
has been re-appointed as chairman of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Established in March 1990, the HKCPEC, structured on a
tripartite basis, is to advise the government on matters related
to Hong Kong's participation in the Pacific Economic Cooperation
Council (PECC).
</P>
<P>
The HKCPEC comprises members from the business, academic and
government sectors. The new-term membership is composed of 24
members, with eight from each of the three sectors. Among the
new-term members, 16 are re-appointed members including its
chairman.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong became a member of PECC in May 1991. The PECC, a
non-governmental organization seeking for closer cooperation on
trade and economic policy issues in the Pacific Region, now has a
total of 23 member-committees representing a number of countries
and regions including Australia, Canada, China, Japan, Korea,
Russia, Singapore and the United States. France joined it as an
associated member in April 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
