<HEADLINE> HK's Construction Output for 1997 Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The gross value of construction
work, in nominal terms, performed by main contractors of Hong Kong
amounted to 130.7 billion HK dollars (16.77 billion U.S. dollars)
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented an increase of 12.4 percent from the
previous year, according to official statistics released Monday.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary results issued by the Census and Statistics
Department showed that the gross value of construction work, in
nominal terms, performed by main contractors increased by 7.2
percent in the fourth quarter of 1997 from the same period in
1996.
</P>
<P>
A local government spokesman said that construction output at
private sector sites rose strongly in 1997, bolstered by robust
building activity. The slowdown in construction output at public
sector sites was attributable mainly to the winding down of
projects under the Airport Core Program, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
