<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower Monday in the absence of
leads as dealers said the market awaited cautiously for Tuesday's
deadline outcome of the proposed merger of finance companies.
</P>
<P>
The market hardly moved from its morning levels and trading was
thin with focus on finance counters, which saw more price erosions
ahead of the possible merger announcements.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 4.66
points to 722.96, the all-share Emas Index dropped 1.74 points to
182.35, the Industrial Index was 7.99 points lower at 1,298.12
while the Second Board Index fell 1.86 points to 179.85.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 530 to 122 while 121 counters were
unchanged and 144 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover was 151.193 million shares worth 349.956
million ringgit (about 97.345 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume dropped to 133.749 million shares worth
309.893 million ringgit (about 86.201 million U.S. dollars) from
165.092 million shares valued at 369.932 million ringgit (about
102.901 million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover dropped also to 17.444 million shares
worth 40.062 million ringgit (about 11.143 million U.S. dollars)
from last week's close at 19.331 million shares valued at 49.724
million ringgit (about 13.831 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals however expanded to 27.852 million shares
worth 84.205 million ringgit (about 23.422 million U.S. dollars)
from 4.590 million shares valued at 23.188 million ringgit (about
6.45 million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.363
million shares traded, industrial products 9.034 million shares,
construction 15.417 million shares, trading/service 29.606
million shares, infrastructure 593,000 shares, finance 30.157
million shares, hotels 511,000 shares, properties 16.485 million
shares, plantation 4.981 million shares, mining 1.029 million
shares, trusts 20,000 shares, closed/fund 200,000 shares and loans
19.351 million shares. 
