<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down Slightly on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined slightly
in moderate trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) lost 5.37 points to close
at 1648.56 points on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The closing of corporate reporting season, stability in
financial markets around the region and lack of fresh factors
contributed to some lethargy in the market, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
They said that with the STII failing to move higher, most
investors decided to square their positions and stay sidelined.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 210.47 million units, valued
at 269.45 million Singapore dollars (168.41 million U.S. dollars).
Declines overwhelmed advances by 315 to 50, while 246 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Uniphoenix was the most actively traded stock as it registered
a turnover of 12.74 million units. It was followed by Renong Bhd
which had 8.74 million shares traded. M. Resources was next with
7.22 million units changed hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA (the Singapore Airlines) Foreign led the gainers of the day
as it rose by 30 cents to finish at 11.7 Singapore dollars. SPH
(Singapore Press Holdings) increased by 20 cents to end at 18.7
Singapore dollars. Auric Pac was up by 18 cents to close at 1.54
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.7 dollars to end at 36.3 Singapore dollars. DBS
(Development Bank of Singapore) fell by 1.4 dollars to close at
8.35 Singapore dollars, while DBS Foreign was 1.3 dollars lower to
finish at 12 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
