<HEADLINE> Chongqing-Nagoya Flight Service Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The first international flight
connecting Chongqing, China's fourth municipality, and Nagoya,
Japan, began service today.
</P>
<P>
China Southwest Airlines has flights every Monday and Thursday
using Boeing 757 aircraft. The air distance is 3,000 kilometers
and takes about four hours.
</P>
<P>
The city's Jiangbei Airport was approved by the State Council
in 1995 to conduct international flights. It has charter flights
to Bangkok, Thailand, and Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The city has close business contacts with Japan, and its trade
volume with that country accounts for 44 percent of the
total. Some Japanese multinational corporations have opened more
than 80 ventures in the city involving 400 million U.S. dollars of
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
