<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newly Appointed Chinese Ministers Discuss Work Goals  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, today has given two pages on the work plans of
15 newly elected ministers.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan, the minister in charge of the State Development
Planning Commission, said the agency gained a role in
macro-economic control as a result of the latest institutional
restructuring while becoming less involved in specific affairs.
</P>
<P>
"From now on, we will focus our effort on the major issues in
national development and strive to do a better job in exercising
macro-economic control," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our first task is to ensure that the economic growth rate will
reach eight percent," Zeng said.
</P>
<P>
Whether the goal can be reached has a bearing on the overall
situation of the national economy and, to realize the goal, China
will take measures to boost domestic demand and increase
infrastructure investment, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sheng Huaren, the minister in charge of the State Economic and
Trade Commission, said his agency is responsible for monitoring
and coordinating the daily operation of the national economy,
promoting state enterprise reforms, readjusting the economic
structure, and formulating and implementing industrial policies
and regulations.
</P>
<P>
"Currently, we are facing the dual tasks of reforming ourselves
and opening up a new situation in economic and trade work," Sheng
said.
</P>
<P>
The commission will take measures to "encourage mergers,
standardize bankruptcies, divert laid-off workers, increase
efficiency, implement the re-employment project, improve the
structure, boost technical advances, open up the market, turn
around losses and increase profits," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Our aim is to ensure that the eight percent economic growth
rate will be realized smoothly and that the large- and medium-size
state-owned enterprises will get out of financial difficulties in
three years," Sheng said, adding that he is personally confident
about doing a good job.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yongkang, the minister of Land and Natural Resources, said
that the work of his ministry is of great significance to both the
rational use and protection of land, minerals, marine resources
and other natural resources and to sustainable economic growth.
</P>
<P>
"I will dedicate myself to work and strive to live up to the
responsibilities bestowed on me by the state and people," he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
