<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newly Appointed Chinese Ministers Discuss Work Goals  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Liu Jibin, the minister in charge of the Commission of Science,
Technology and Industry for National Defense, said that those
industries are strategic for the national economy and are at a
crucial development stage.
</P>
<P>
"We will, in line with the special characteristics of our
industry, form large enterprise groups of different types to meet
market competition," he said.
</P>
<P>
Liu added that his commission will beef up efforts to readjust
the industrial structure, size and layout as well as research and
production capacity.
</P>
<P>
"I will strive to be a servant of the people and not fall short
of their expectations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Huaicheng, the minister of Finance, said that one of the
main tasks of his ministry is to sensibly fine-tune fiscal
macro-economic controls to increase domestic demand and boost
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
While the fiscal deficit and debt level are controlled, efforts
will be made to make good use of the current fiscal resources and
improve the expenditure structure, he said.
</P>
<P>
Investment will be increased in agriculture, science and
technology, and infrastructure and public utilities, Xiang said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that other tasks of his ministry include
supporting reforms, increasing fiscal revenues and beefing up
spending management.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zuoji, the minister of Labor and Social Security, said
the main objectives of his ministry are to strive to establish in
three-to-five years a labor and social security system suited to
the development level of the productivity of the primary stage of
socialism and that meets the needs of a socialist market economic
system.
</P>
<P>
His ministry now encounters three difficulties: the diversion
and re-employment of workers laid off by state-owned enterprises,
the problem of an aging population, and people's increasing needs
for medical services, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the three problems relate to the personal
interests of residents and therefore must be resolved properly.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be increased for re-employment, reforms in the
medical insurance system, and unified management of social
insurance, among others, Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
Yu Zhengsheng, the minister of Construction, said that his
ministry will first of all take measures to boost housing
construction to make it a new economic growth area.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will also be made to tackle the new situation and new
problems cropping up in the process of urbanization, implement the
Construction Law, and reform the traditional industries through
scientific and technical advances, Yu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
