<HEADLINE> Newly Appointed Chinese Ministers Discuss Work Goals (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 15 Chinese ministers all stressed the importance of being
efficient and honest and to strive to push the country's reform
and development, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Fu Zhihuan, the minister of the Railways, said his
agency would lead workers of the entire railway sector in
expanding the reform of the railway industry and stepping up
construction during his five-year tenure.
</P>
<P>
According to Fu, the reform measures will separate railway
administrative functions from the functions of production; let
railway administrative departments, industrial enterprises and
construction firms practice independent accounting and bear sole
responsibility for profits and losses; cut the workforce by 1.1
million to improve efficiency in the coming three years; and
reduce losses and increase profits step by step. Fu also set a
goal of eliminating losses in the entire railway sector by 2000.
</P>
<P>
In the coming five years, China will spend 250 billion yuan on
railway construction.
</P>
<P>
Huang Zhendong, the minister of the Communications, said that
during his tenure, concentrated efforts will be made to do a good
job of accelerating infrastructure construction for
transportation, restructuring administrative departments, stepping
up the introduction of a legal system for transportation, and
successfully operating large- and medium-size state-owned
transport enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The ministry of the Information Industry includes the former
ministries of posts and telecommunications, the electronics
industry and some related departments of the former ministry of
radio, film and television to meet the demands of the modern
technological revolution and advance development of China's
information industry.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the tasks and concerned responsibilities entrusted
to the new ministry are heavy and great, said new Information
Industry Minister Wu Jichuan.
</P>
<P>
Wu pledged to expand reform and open wider to the outside
world, formulate policies on advancing the information industry by
persisting in proceeding from China's actual conditions, and to
live up to the trust and expectations of the Chinese Communist
Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
Niu Maosheng, the minister of the Water Resources , vowed to
make a success of his agency by completing three tasks which
include tightening a unified management of water resources and
advancing sustainable development, accelerating infrastructure
construction for water control and bringing about a coordinated
development of water resources and the national economy,
vigorously advancing the industrialization of water resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
