<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Newly Appointed Chinese Ministers Discuss Work Goals (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shi Guangsheng, the minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC), said the central task for the moment is to
increase exports and attract more overseas funds, overcome
various kinds of difficulties and ensure a steady increase in
China's foreign trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
To accomplish the central task, MOFTEC will keep improving the
export commodity structure, fully expand overseas markets,
intensify efforts to attract overseas funds, make a success of
project contracting and labor service cooperation, successfully
reform overseas aid programs, help more powerful Chinese
enterprises invest abroad, and pursue new development
opportunities and markets, said Shi.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural Minister Chen Yaobang pledged to build a solid
agricultural base by implementing major policies and measures for
stabilizing agriculture and the rural economy, doing a good job of
capital construction in farming to change weak agricultural
conditions, making a success of using science and technology to
invigorate agriculture, stabilizing the team of technical
personnel, and improving the training of rural officials.
</P>
<P>
Chen also urged greater efforts to ensure good annual
harvests. It is expected that this year China will harvest 490
billion kilograms of grain, and farmers' per capita net income
will also go up by 5 percent, and another 10 million of the
country's entire 58 million people people will rise above the
poverty line.
</P>
<P>
The Auditor-General of the National Audit Office, Li Jinhua,
said his office will tighten auditing over financial affairs of
government departments, state-owned financial institutions and
government institutions to ensure the safety and efficient use of
state revenues and funds strictly in accordance with relevant
laws. His office also will introduce an auditing and inspection
system meeting the demands of a socialist market economy in
five-to-10 years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, present of the People's Bank, the central bank,
said the central government has drawn up a three-year program to
build a financial organization, market mechanisms, and a financial
control and regulatory system adaptable to the demands of
developing China's socialist market economy. This would improve
the operation and management standards of the financial service,
bring about a marked improvement in the country's financial order,
improve China's capacity to prevent and combat financial risks,
and create favorable conditions for expanding China's opening-up
and modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Dai pledged to fulfill the tasks by expanding reform and
striving to construct a modern financial setup and working system,
implementing relevant money and credit policies correctly to
ensure that China will attain its macro-economic adjustment goals
in structural adjustments to the national economy, tighten
supervision and regulation to prevent financial risks and build a
financial order featuring legally binding operations and fair
competition, tighten the management of foreign exchanges and
foreign debts, maintain an international balance of payments, and
safeguard the stability of the exchange rates for Chinese currency
against hard currencies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
