<HEADLINE> Derailment Paralyzes Railroad in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 30 (Xinhua) -- The derailment of a cargo train in
southwestern Iran has blocked the railroad linking Tehran, the
capital, and Khuzestan Province, the Iranian official news agency
IRNA reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Two cars of the train ran off the railway on Sunday in Lorestan
Province hours after the train left Ahvaz, Khuzestan's capital,
for Tehran, IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
But it did not say whether there were any casualties in the
incident.
</P>
<P>
A group of railway experts rushed to the scene to probe into
the incident and help reopen the railroad, IRNA added.
</P>
<P>
Many cases of derailment were reported in Iran during recent
years and most of the incidents were caused by either carelessness
of the train drivers or the poor conditions of the tracks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
