<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forest Fires Rage in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 30 (Xinhua)-- Some 490 forest fires raged in
Vietnam's 19 provinces in the first three months of this year,
destroying 7,948 hectares of forests.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnam News Agency reported Monday that the figure
presents a sharp increase over that of last year which saw a total
of 1,424 hectares of forests destroyed by 295 fires.
</P>
<P>
Prolonged drought, widespread slash-and-burn farming in the
northern and central regions, and the use of fire in the
restricted areas in the south were the main causes of the forest
fires, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Low water levels in reservoirs near the forests also worsened
the problem, it added.
</P>
<P>
In a move to minimize forest fires, the Vietnamese government
has ordered all provinces and cities to take urgent measures in
forest fire prevention and fighting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
