<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Police Urges Companies to Step up Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Police Monday appealed
companies in Hong Kong using glass doors with digital locks at
their main entrances to step up security by latching both the
upper and lower parts of the doors.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was issued by a police spokesman after six companies
in commercial buildings in Ngau Tau Kok, Hong Kong, were burgled
earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The company operators had left one of the two latches of the
glass doors off, thus allowing burglars to gain assess to the
premises easily, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said: "The glass doors had not been properly locked unless
the doors were fastened by both the upper and lower latches."
</P>
<P>
Police believed that the culprits entered the premises by
inserting a metal plate or a hard object to release the latch.
There was no need for them to prize the locks, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The victimized companies suffered a total loss of 81,300 in
cash and valuable items in the burglaries which occurred between
March 2 and 14.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
