<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Hotels Facing New Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hotels in China are urged to grasp
the international trend and nurture a good enterprise culture in a
timely manner to meet future challenges.
</P>
<P>
China now has 5,000 tourism hotels, of which most were built to
cope with traditional tourism characteristic of large-scale,
package tours with low prices and standard services, said experts
at a recent hotel industry seminar here.
</P>
<P>
However, as the worldwide travel industry entered a new year,
tourists' needs are expected to become more diverse and spur a
demand for more variety in hotels.
</P>
<P>
As more tourists plan to visit China, international hotel
giants are preparing to enter the China market, which will
increase competition, they said.
</P>
<P>
"Facing new opportunities and challenges, we have a mixed
feeling of hope and anxiety," one expert said.
</P>
<P>
Hotel experts from 24 provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities attended the seminar held in Haikou this month.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
