<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe's Longest Bridge Opens to Traffic in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Europe's longest bridge was put to
use Sunday as Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio cut the ribbon at
the opening ceremony here.
</P>
<P>
The bridge, named after Vasco da Gama, the famous Portuguese
navigator of the late 15th and early 16th centuries, measures 17.2
kilometers long in total, with 10 kilometers running over Tejo
River to link up the northern and southern parts of Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
Official reports said that it took 3,300 workers three
years to build this bridge in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The cable-stay bridge, which cost 1.1 billion U.S. dollars, is
expected to play an important part in easing the long-standing
traffic problem in Lisbon, especially during the World Fair season
scheduled for May in the Portuguese capital city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
