<HEADLINE> Colombia Draws Paraguay 1-1 in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Colombia and Paraguay played
to a 1-1 draw in their pre-World Cup exhibition game in New Haven,
Connecticut on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Miguel Benitez equalised for Paraguay at 42nd minute
after Colombia scored the opener at 12th through midfielder Alex
Comas.
</P>
<P>
Goalkeeper Miguel Calero, who made his debut with the Colombian
national team, made three saves.
</P>
<P>
"For sure, I wasn't happy with the result," Paraguay's coach
Paulo Cesar Carpegiani said, "we had chances, particularly in the
second half. We should have done better."
</P>
<P>
Colombia coach Hernan Dario Gomez was unavailable after the
game.
</P>
<P>
Colombian midfield Carlos Valderrama set the tone of the first
half with an early shot at 1:20 into the match.
</P>
<P>
After three more missed shots, Comas tapped the ball at the top
of the penalty box, pasted one defender and slammed it into the
lower right corner of the net.
</P>
<P>
Before the half break, Benitez stole the ball from two
defenders and drilled his shot into the lower corner for the tie.
</P>
