<HEADLINE> Chongqing Welcomes Hong Kong Investors in State-owned Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing welcomes Hong Kong
companies' participation in the restructuring of its state-owned
enterprises (SOE), said Yang Taiqi, vice director of the Municipal
Economic Committee.
</P>
<P>
As the largest industrial center in southwest China, Chongqing
has established a modern enterprise system in 100 of its more than
300 large and medium SOEs and reformed other ailing SOEs through
mergers, bankruptcies and closures. The city plans to restructure
many medium and small SOEs with the help of overseas investment
and participation, Yang said.
</P>
<P>
"Chongqing welcomes large Hong Kong companies to form
multinational companies with local large SOEs with sales exceeding
2-to-10 billion yuan each," Yang said.
</P>
<P>
Medium and small enterprises in Hong Kong will also get the
opportunity to take part in restructuring local medium and small
enterprises by merger, shareholding, contracted operation and
joint investment.
</P>
<P>
The city especially needs investors to develop high-tech
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
With abundant labor resources, cheaper land than coastal areas
and a huge market potential with 30 million population, Chongqing
is an ideal place for investment, Yang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
