<HEADLINE> India Extends Loan to Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 30 (Xinhua) -- India has agreed to extend a loan
of 10 million U.S. dollars to Myanmar for carrying out projects of
the country's two ministries, The New Light of Myanmar newspaper
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for India to provide such a loan to
Myanmar in recent years.
</P>
<P>
According to the loan agreement between the two governments
signed here Sunday, the loan will be used for production of
machines and technical services of the Myanmar Ministry of Rail
Transportation and the Ministry of Industry No.2.
</P>
<P>
India offered financial assistance to Myanmar last year for the
joint implementation of a 160-kilometer Tamu-Kalay-Kalaywa motor
road upgrading project in Tamu, a Myanmar border town, to
facilitate border trade between the two countries. 
</P>
