<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gypsy Woman in Bulgaria Gives Birth to 22 Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- A Bulgarian woman recently gave
birth to her 22nd child, making a record in the country's history,
reported the biggest Bulgarian newspaper, Dneven Trud, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Teventana Stefanova, a 38-year-old Gypsy woman living in the
Kisselevo suburb of the north Bulgaria city of Lom, got married at
the age of 15.
</P>
<P>
From then on, she has been giving birth at the rate of one
child one year.
</P>
<P>
Stefanova and her husband, together with their 15 kids, are now
living in a house without electricity and water. Their seven
grown-up children had left them to make a living by their own.
</P>
<P>
Due to a decline in birth rate and a rise in morality,
Bulgaria's population has been continuously dropping in recent
years.
</P>
<P>
However, the Gypsy population still maintained a high birth
rate, with the past six years seeing some 12,000 Gypsy newborns,
or 20 percent out of the total of 60,000.
</P>
<P>
Most of the Gypsy families are living in poverty as a result of
raising too many children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
