<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hakkinen Wins Brazilian F1 Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Mika Hakkinen dominated the
Brazilian Grand Prix in Sao Paulo on Sunday, winning his third
consecutive victory.
</P>
<P>
His McLaren teammate David Coulthard helped for a 1-2 finish by
coming in second.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Hakkinen of Finland, who won the Grand Prix in
Australia and the last race of the 1997 season, flew to the lead
as soon as the green light went on and never let go.
</P>
<P>
He completed the 72-lap race around the 4.292-kilometer track
in one hour 37 minutes and 11.747 seconds, just 1.102 seconds
ahead of his Scottish teammate.
</P>
<P>
More than one minute behind Hakkinen was Germany's Michael
Schumacher of the Ferrari team who completed the race in
1:38:12.297.
</P>
<P>
Coulthard said there was no pre-race agreement like in the
Australian Grand Prix where he pulled aside in the final minutes
to let Hakkinen win.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Jacques Villeneuve finished in 7th, saying
"it was a disappointing race ... we had a problem with the rear
end of the car." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0223 </DOCNO>
