<HEADLINE> Poland Wins World Cup Sabre Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Poland defeated Italy 45 to 36
to win the 1998 Sabre World Cup here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory also awarded Poland the overall World Cup sabre
championship as well as the event was the last of eight World Cup
sabre competitions this season and the overall championship.
</P>
<P>
The members of Poland's team are Norbert Jaskot, Dariusz
Gilman, Tomasz Pigula, Edmund Sznajder and Stefan Sobala.
</P>
<P>
Russia finished third in the 18-team competition, followed by
Romania, Germany, Spain and the United States.
</P>
<P>
In the individual competition Saturday, Damien Touya of France,
the top-ranked man in the world, defeated 1997 world champion
Stanislav Pozdniakov of Russia. 
