The Ministry of Science and Technology will continue pioneering
technological innovation and developing high-tech industries to
meeting the world's challenges, Zhu Lilan, the recently appointed
minister said.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Council has issued a circular urging local
governments and departments to strengthen tax administration and
carry out state taxation laws to the letter.
</P>
<P>
-- China will invest 245 billion yuan (29.5 billion US dollars)
in railway construction in the next five years, China Daily
learned at a high-level railway conference.  
</P>
