<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rios Beats Agassi to Win Lipton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Marcelo Rios of Chile claimed
the world number one ranking on Sunday by beating American Andre
Agassi 7-5, 6-3, 6-4 in the final of the Lipton Tennis
Championships at key Biscayne, Florida.
</P>
<P>
Rios became the first South American to reach the top of the
rankings and the 14th player to achieve number one status in the
25-year history of the ranking system.
</P>
<P>
Rios' victory Sunday ended Pete Sampras' 102 consecutive weeks
in the top spot. Sampras has been number one for a total of 218
weeks over his career.
</P>
<P>
Rios has won the BellSouth Open in Auckland in January and at
the Indian Wells event leading up to the Lipton. He also reached
the final of the Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
Both Agassi and Rios came to the final match with identical
24-3 records for the year.
</P>
<P>
Rios blasted 12 aces past Agassi and scored 48 outright winners
to Agassi's 25 in the one hour, 57 minute match.
</P>
<P>
Agassi pulled back from 4-1 down in the first set to even the
score at 4-4, but Rios's game was too strong for him.
</P>
<P>
In the final game of the first set, on Rios's fourth set point
of the game, Agassi double faulted to give the Chilean the lead
and from then, Rios was in charge of the match.
</P>
<P>
He broke Agassi's serve in the fourth game of the second set
and the seventh game of the third set to earn the straight sets
victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980330.0231 </DOCNO>
