<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, March 30 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greek Defense Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos discussed
Sunday with his visiting Albanian counterpart, Sabit Brokaj, the
establishment of a multinational peacekeeping force in the Balkan
region, the situation in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo and the
recent upsurge in crime in Greece.
</P>
<P>
During their talks which took place in the northwestern Greek
town of Ioannina, the two ministers agreed that the Balkan Defense
Undersecretaries meet again in the Albanian capital of Tirana on
May 21, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported
Sunday. (Greece-Albania-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A huge explosion blasted Sunday night in the West
Bank city Ramallah, killing two people and injuring several
others, Israeli army radio said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place in a residential neighborhood where
the office of Jibril Rajoub, a Palestinian official in charge of
security in the West Bank, is situated. The cause of the explosion
was not immediate known, the report said.
(Palestine-Ramallah-Blast)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- A Peruvian air force cargo plane carrying dozens of
civilian passengers crashed Sunday in northern Peru, killing at
least 12 people, officials said.
</P>
<P>
"The plane was carrying about 40 passengers. It seems between
15 and 20 people have died," Miguel Ciccia, a congressman told
Radio Programas, a local radio station.
</P>
<P>
But police could not confirm the death toll. A local hospital
director said that 12 people were killed and 39 others injured
when the Russian-made Antonov plane went down. (Peru-Air-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- The Paris-based International Trade Chamber (ITC) has
set up its Middle East regional council to boost commercial,
banking, insurance and other business cooperation among its member
countries, an ITC official said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, Syria, Lebanon and the Saudi Arabia have become the
first batch of countries winning the regional council membership
which is limited to the Arab countries in the region only,
Mohammad Asfur, president of ITC Amman Chapter, was quoted by
Jordan's official news agency as saying. (Jordan-ITC)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Fighting is continuing in eastern Sierra Leone as the
west African peace-keeping force (ECOMOG) encounters pockets of
resistance from remnants of the ousted military junta.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ECOMOG's pro-government ally of hunters militiamen
known as the Kamajors is gaining grounds in Kalohon and
neighboring districts in the eastern border area with Liberia, the
British Broadcasting Corporation reported Sunday.
(SLeone-Fighting) 
</P>
