<HEADLINE> Hainan Province to Ask Each Resident to Protect One Tree </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 30 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Province will launch a
campaign in June asking that each person protect one tree.
</P>
<P>
The campaign has targeted 300,000 trees in three state or
provincial nature reserves in the Wuzhi, Jianfeng, and Bawang
mountains of this tropical island province in south China.
</P>
<P>
Each volunteer will be granted a special badge and every tree
protected will bear a card indicating its name, age, and the name
of its protector.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the State Bureau of Environmental Protection and
the Ministry of Education, the campaign aims to increase public
awareness on environmental protection. 
</P>
