<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Franceschina Sets 500m World Record in Speed Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Nicola Franceschina beat the
500 meters world record at the Team World Championships short
track speedskating in Bormio, Italy, on Sunday as Canada and China
took the men and women overall titles respectively.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Franceschina became the first man to skate
under 42 seconds in the 500 in 41.938 seconds, eclipsing the mark
of 42.458 set by Chinese Feng Kai in Vienna a week ago.
</P>
<P>
Franceschina's performance helped Italy finish third in the
men's competition with 42 points, behind Canada and defending
champion South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Canada, led by Marc Gagnon's victories at 1,000 and 3,000
meters, totaled 48 points to South Korea's 45.
</P>
<P>
China dominated the women's events, collecting 61 points with
eight victories in 11 races, while South Korea had to settle for
another silver medal with 49 points, seven better than third-place
Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
