<HEADLINE> Italian Gaudenzi Wins Morocco Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Andrea Gaudenzi of Italy outpowered
his Spaniard opponent Alex Calatrava 6-4, 5-7, 6-4 to win the
Grand Prix Hassan II tennis tournament in Casablanca, Morocco on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
This was the first career title for the 24-year-old Gaudenzi,
who currently ranked 57th in the world and had failed in his
previous five finals.
</P>
<P>
"The difference between the finals I lost and today was that
here I played aggressively on every important point," said
Gaudenzi who will join in the top 50 for the first time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
