<HEADLINE> Tanzanian, Kenyan Win Los Angeles Marathons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 29 (Xinhua) -- Zebedayo Bayo of Tanzania and
Lorna Kiplagat of Kenya became the winners of the men's and
women's marathon races here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Bayo ran the fastest in the men's group by
clocking in 2 hours 11 minutes 21 seconds, while 23-year-old
Kiplagat retained her title in 2:34:03.
</P>
<P>
Bayo outraced Jonathan Ndambuki of Kenya in the final uphill
climb with the latter finished four seconds back at 2:11:25.
</P>
<P>
Two Kenyans finished third and fourth as Simon Lopuyet clocked
in 2:11:41 and Philip Chirchir timed in 2:11:52. Mexico's
Alejandro Cruz was fifth in 2:12:27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
